    {
      "changeIds": [
        "pr:nightscout/Trio#1219",
        "pr:nightscout/Trio#1224"
      ],
      "summary": "Ensure PumpManager receives DeliveryLimits built from the user’s PumpSettings at initialization to avoid stale/default limits causing silent rejection of temp basals. Adds DeliveryLimitsSyncTests to verify maxBasal→maximumBasalRate and maxBolus→maximumBolus mappings. Also includes related release bookkeeping (app version bump to 0.8.3), OmnipodKit submodule update, blacklist updates, and minor UI text cleanup. PR #1224 syncs the v0.8.3 patch (including #1219) back into dev.",
      "userFacingImpact": "This hotfix is intended to prevent `.invalidSetting` failures caused by a stale delivery-limits value and to stop silent rejections of temp basals by forcing the pump manager to receive the user’s current delivery limits on init. Tests were added to guard the mapping. The PR and its sync into dev include release/version bookkeeping and submodule updates that do not, by themselves, indicate additional behavioral changes.",
